Abiodun Nejo, Ado Ekiti The police in Ekiti State have arraigned a 22-year-old man, Mohammed Yusuf, before an Ado-Ekiti Chief Magistratesâ€™ Court for allegedly stealing some aluminium window frames. Yusuf is facing a count of stealing. The police prosecutor, Inspector Oriyomi Akinwale, alleged that the defendant stole some aluminium window frames valued at N50,000 belonging to one Kayode Oladipupo. Akinwale told the court that Yusuf committed the offence around 3pm on December 30, 2019, at the Ekute Quarter, Ado-Ekiti. The police prosecutor said the offence contravened Section 390 (9) of the Criminal Code, Laws of Ekiti State, 2012. He asked the court for an adjournment to enable him to study the case file and assemble his witnesses. The defendant pleaded not guilty. Counsel for the defendant, Mr Emmanuel Sumonu, urged the court to grant him bail with a promise that he would not jump bail. The Chief Magistrate, Mr Adesoji Adegboye, granted the accused bail in the sum of N50,000 with one surety in like sum. He adjourned the case till February 14, 2020, for hearing. Copyright PUNCH.
